Just a day after Education Cabinet secretary&nbsp;professor George Magoha&nbsp;gave a blanket directive to secondary school heads&nbsp;to send home learners with fee balances, stakeholders have raised concerns over the government&rsquo;s approach to the matter. Some head teachers say the directive is not&nbsp;easy to implement. This even as the Kenya Union for Post Primary Education Teachers, KUPPET, says the directive contravenes the right of all children to free and compulsory education